<!DOCTYPE html>
<html data-ng-app="spaceFrontierApp">
<% include header %>

<body id="home" data-ng-controller="homeController">   
    <section class="module parallax parallax-large parallax-1" style="width:100%; top: 0;">
        <div class="container" id="parallax">
            <h1>SPACE Tool</h1>
            <h3>Science Payloads and Advanced Concepts for Exploration Interactive</h3>
            <p>Provides a basic system for a deep space CubeSat based off of user specifications for a mission</p>
            <div class="row" style="text-align:center; color: white">
                <a id="rcorners" href="/tool" class="btn btn-lg" style="color: #FFFFFF;">Let's Begin!</a>
            </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module content" style="width:100%">
        <div class="container" style="width:%">
            <h1 style="text-align:center; font-size:50px">What Are CubeSats?</h1>
            <hr>
            <p>CubeSats are small satellites grouped under the umbrella category of nano-satellites, coming in units that are each 10 cm x 10 cm x 10 cm, weighing about 1.33 kg. A CubeSat can, and often, consists of multiple units of various configurations depending on the mission requirements.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module parallax parallax-small parallax-2" style="width:100%">
    <div class="container" id="parallax">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-2" style="width:%">
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-10" style="width:%">
                <p><br></p>
                <p style="text-align:right; font-size:30px">
                In 1999, Bob Twiggs and Jordi Purig-Surai introduced a new satellite blueprint to allow graduate students to develop and test small, low cost spacecrafts. Their intended target was Low-Earth Orbit. Since then, the idea of low cost space exploration has become increasingly popular. Private companies and research institutions manufacture low volume, low cost parts specifically for CubeSats.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>


    <section class="module content">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 style="text-align:center; font-size:50px">Why CubeSats?</h1>
            <hr>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="group">
                    <div class="col-lg-3" style="margin-left:-100px">
                        <div class="card effect__hover">
                            <div class="card__front">
                                <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:60px;">Entry to Deep Space</p></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card__back">
                                <span class="card__text"><br>CubeSats already <br>exist in Low-Earth Orbit, but <br>we hope the next stage of develop-<br>ment will send them deeper into our solar system.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3">
                        <div class="card effect__hover">
                            <div class="card__front">
                                <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:65px;">Form Factor</p></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card__back">
                                <span class="card__text"><br>The shape and size of <br>CubeSats make them sturdier <br> than their larger counterparts, which <br>require more structural planning.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3">
                        <div class="card effect__hover">
                            <div class="card__front">
                                <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:60px;">Standardized Platform</p></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card__back">
                                <span class="card__text"><br>There are <br>several planned and tested <br>methods of deployment, which range from swarms of satellites to individual releases. </span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3">
                        <div class="card effect__hover">
                            <div class="card__front">
                                <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:60px;">More Scientific Returns</p></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card__back">
                                <span class="card__text"><br>By launching <br> several CubeSats with varied <br>instruments, scientists can achieve<br> a more dynamic view of the target. </span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="dividerlargest"></div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-3" style="margin-left:-100px">
                    <div class="card effect__hover">
                        <div class="card__front">
                            <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:65px;">Predictability<p></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card__back">
                            <span class="card__text"><br>The standardization of <br>CubeSats will reduce the risks <br>associated with launches, which is a substantial concerns for large-scale satellites.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-3">
                    <div class="card effect__hover">
                        <div class="card__front">
                            <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:55px;">Reduced Launch Costs</p></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card__back">
                            <span class="card__text"><br>Launch costs for space <br>equipment vary with mass. <br>Currently, it costs roughly $10k/lb to reach earth orbit. Due to their form factor, the launch costs will be substantially reduced.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-3">
                    <div class="card effect__hover">
                        <div class="card__front">
                            <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:40px;">Multiple <br>Platform Missions</p></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card__back">
                            <span class="card__text"><br>CubeSats may be <br>configured in "swarms", groups<br> that follow a similar trajectory and research one objective, which gives<br> the mission more room for errors.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-3">
                    <div class="card effect__hover">
                        <div class="card__front">
                            <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:60px;">Disruptive Science!</p></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card__back">
                            <span class="card__text"><br>CubeSats will disrupt the<br> way exploration is being carried<br> out and will bring us back to the age<br> of fearless exploration.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="dividerbiggest"></div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module parallax parallax-small parallax-3">
    <div class="container" id="parallax">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4">
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-8">
                <p style="text-align:right; font-size:35px"><br><br><br><br>To date, there have been over 300 CubeSat missions. The list continues to grow!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module content">
        <div class="container">
            <h3 style="text-align:center; font-size:50px">Challenges Facing Deep Space Cubesats</h3>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:120px">Short Lifespan</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>CubeSats have an average lifespan of one year in Low Earth Orbit. However, as deep space developments take place, improved propulsion systems may increase this length.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:100px">Form Factor Limits for Fuel/Propulsion Units</p></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>The standardized volume of CubeSats decreases the room available for propulsion systems. Efficient use of this space may be the key to extending CubeSat lifespan.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div style="background-image:url(/img/2.jpg); background-size:cover" class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>An artist's depiction of 3 single unit (1U) CubeSats in Earth Orbit. This is a "swarm" configuration.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:100px">Increased Radiation</br>Levels</p></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text">Deep Space CubeSats must tolerate more radiation because they do not fall under the protection of Earth's magnetic field. In order to make CubeSats durable, scientists must devise a means of protection, especially for the electronics of the CubeSat.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="dividertinier"></div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div style="background-image:url(/img/1.jpg); background-size:cover" class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard_text"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>An artist's depiction of a single, multi-unit CubeSat in Earth Orbit.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover" id="2">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:70px">Greater Communication Range</p></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>CubeSats require a stronger signal to communicate with scientists when they move farther from the Earth.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:100px">Generation of Power Farther from the Sun</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text">As they move away from Low-Earth Orbit, CubeSats will receive less sunlight. As many CubeSats rely on solar panels for energy, this will present a challenge. New solar panels have a deployable configuration, which allows them to capture more sunlight.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div style="background-image:url(/img/3.jpg); background-size:cover" class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>An artist's illustration of 2 multi-unit CubeSats in Lunar Orbit. The image displays deployable solar panels.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <hr>
            <h1>Where We Come In!</h1>
            <p>Here at Goddard Space Flight Center, we have developed an online CubeSat design tool, geared towards deep space exploration based on a specific mission requirement. This tool is ideal for scientists and engineers who wants to draw up a complete, but preliminary system, consisting of parts that are a mixture of commercial off the shelf, as well as research innovations specifically designed for the deep space environment – making the overall cost much more manageable. SPACE walks the user through a series of questions and forms, eventually parsing these parts together for a final design consisting of seven separate subsystems. We hope that with the development of this tool, we can eventually move towards a standardization of the CubeSat paradigm, making it cheaper, faster, and easier than ever to design a CubeSat.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module parallax parallax-small parallax-4">
    <div class="container" id="parallax">
        <div class="dividersmall"></div>
        <h1><a href="/tool" style="color:white">Create your CubeSat today!</a></h1>
    </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="container">
        <% include footer %>
    </div>
    <div class = "divider"></div>
</body>
</html>

         